0","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","Abt 1294":"circa 1294","1314":"1314","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","about 1310":"circa 1310","before 1294":"vóór 1294","Abt 1270":"circa 1270","Abt 24 June 1314":"circa 24 juni 1314","Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Banff, Scotland":"Banffshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Europe":"Europa","Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland":"Cullen, Banffshire, Schotland","Cairny Barclay, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Schotland"},"en":{"Abt 1270–Abt 24 June 1314":"about 1270–about 24 June 1314","1270–1314":"1270–1314","–Female":"Deceased","1294–1350":"1294–1350","1305–Female":"1305–Deceased","1310–Male":"1310–Deceased","1245–1314":"1245–1314","1220–Female":"1220–Deceased","1220":"1220","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","Abt 1294":"about 1294","1314":"1314","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","about 1310":"about 1310","before 1294":"before 1294","Abt 1270":"about 1270","Abt 24 June 1314":"about 24 June 1314","Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Banff, Scotland":"Banffshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Europe":"Europe","Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland":"Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland","Cairny Barclay, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Barclay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name of English origin, from any of several places so called, such as Berkley in Somerset or Berkeley in Gloucestershire, both named in Old English with <i>be(o)rc</i> ‘birch’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","History: The surname was brought to Scotland from southwestern England in the 12th century; Walter de Berchelai or Berkelai was Chamberlain of Scotland in 1165. It was long assumed that they were from the family that held Berkeley Castle in Gloucestershire, but the historian G. W. S. Barrow (1973, <i>The Kingdom of the Scots</i>) adduced evidence that they are more probably from Berkley in Somerset."],"variants":[{"name":"Barkley","meanings":["English and northern Irish (Antrim): variant of   Barclay  .","Americanized form of German   Berkel   or of some other similar (like-sounding) German surname."]},{"name":"Barclift","meanings":["Perhaps an altered form of Scottish   Barclay  ."]},{"name":"Berkeley","meanings":["English: habitational name from one or more of the numerous places so named, such as Berkeley in Gloucestershire, named in Old English with <i>be(o)rc</i> ‘birch’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. Compare Scottish   Barclay  .","Jewish (American): adoption of the English surname (see 1 above) in place of   Berkowitz  ."]},{"name":"Brickley","meanings":["English and Irish: metathesized form of   Barclay  ."]}]},{"name":"David","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the greatest of all the kings of Israel, whose history is recounted with great vividness in the first and second books of Samuel and elsewhere. As a boy he killed the giant Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When David Barclay was born about 1270, in Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland, his father, David Barclay, was 26 and his mother, Lady David Barclay Sr., was 52. He married Agatha Barclay before 1294, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died about 24 June 1314, in Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 45."},"et":{"Abt 1270–Abt 24 June 1314":"umbes 1270–umbes 24. juuni 1314","1270–1314":"1270–1314","–Female":"Surnud","1294–1350":"1294–1350","1305–Female":"1305–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1245–1314":"1245–1314","1220–Female":"1220–Surnud","1220":"1220","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","Abt 1294":"umbes 1294","1314":"1314","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","about 1310":"umbes 1310","before 1294":"enne 1294","Abt 1270":"umbes 1270","Abt 24 June 1314":"umbes 24. juuni 1314","Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Banff, Scotland":"Banffshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Europe":"Europe","Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland":"Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland","Cairny Barclay, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fi":{"Abt 1270–Abt 24 June 1314":"noin 1270–noin 24. kesäkuuta 1314","1270–1314":"1270–1314","–Female":"Kuollut","1294–1350":"1294–1350","1305–Female":"1305–Kuollut","1310–Male":"1310–Kuollut","1245–1314":"1245–1314","1220–Female":"1220–Kuollut","1220":"1220","1350":"1350","1294":"1294","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","Abt 1294":"noin 1294","1314":"1314","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","about 1310":"noin 1310","before 1294":"ennen vuotta 1294","Abt 1270":"noin 1270","Abt 24 June 1314":"noin 24. kesäkuuta 1314","Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Bannockburn, Stirlingshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Banff, Scotland":"Banffshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Europe":"Europe","Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland":"Cullen, Banffshire, Scotland","Cairny Barclay, Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fife, Scotland":"Fife, Scotland"},"fr":{"